	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Quietust</b> [ Tue Nov 08, 2005 12:26 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />1. The Japanese release of Contra <strong>IS NOT GRYZOR</strong> - it is 魂斗羅, read as コントラ == KONTORA == <strong>Contra</strong>. Anyone who tells you that the Japanese version is named "Gryzor" is an idiot and/or a liar. (for the record, Cowering falls into the first category)
<br />
<br />2. The Japanese version of Contra uses all eight 1KB CHR ROM banks to their fullest extent, so adapting it to MMC3 (which only has four 1KB banks and two 2KB banks) would require <em>significant</em> additional modifications.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


